PoA on Saturday and Sunday (28th and 29th TWO DAYS)<br>
<br>
<br>
This is not a typical CoG raid where you sign up and I get the first 40 people and put them on the list.  This is a joint effort with Allied Giants, with management assistance from Shadow Fates, and CoG.<br>
<br>
How this raid works, is Allied Giants is primary in supplying the people, I will then fill in the gaps as I see fit to ensure a successful raid.  Therefore, if you sign up, doesn't mean you will be selected.  I will only select you if we are short on Paladins, Bards, Enchanters, Rangers, Warriors, etc...  Whatever I feel is necessary to make a successful raid.  This raid is what I call a prelude to PoA raids for CoG.  Sort of a test with the best possible groups, experienced management, etc...<br>
<br>
Now, I not trying to discourage people from signing up, just keep in mind out of 50 people that may sign up, I may only select 10 to participate.  Also, if you're a Ranger or something, don't say to yourself, &quot;Rangers are never sought, so no point in me signing up.&quot;  Every class has it's use, and I will be selecting from every class.  Obviously enchanters will have an extra edge when signing up, they are of extreme neccessity on that plane.<br>
<br>
Keep in mind the costs for this raid will be expensive.  We may have to purchase coffins, cost for the trip up, pearls for summoning people.<br>
<br>
Also, Im still discussing battle stragety and politics with Allied Giants.  Whatever different things are decided upon, I will still ensure treasure is fair.  However, Allied Giant will have priority as far as personnel are concerned.<br>
<br>
Okay, so that's the general idea.  This is still evolving and can change at a moments notice.<br>
<br>
Also if this is a two day raid, please do not sign up if you have any intention of not showing for the next day.<br>
<br>
